DOC.criteria: Inclusion : Written inform consent Age : ≥ 50 year ≤ 75 year Bilateral age relate cataract , extract followed implantation Posterior Chamber Intraocular Lenses ( IOLs ) Preoperative postoperative astigmatism ≤ 1 Diopter ( D ) , Keratometry read Potential post operative Visual Acuity ( VA ) ≥ 20/40 Second eye surgery take place longer 45 day first implant Exclusion : Irregular optical aberration ; Pupil diameter scotopic condition 6 mm Degenerative visual pathology ( ex : Agerelated Macular Degeneration ( AMD ) ) Other exclusion ReSTOR Directions Use ( DFU )
